ReservoirSample.ReservoirSamplingStrategy
Enclosing class:
ReservoirSample
public static class ReservoirSample.RType
extends ReservoirSample.AbstractStrategy

Type R strategy computes for every object of the underlying iterator the designated position in the reservoir. If the computed position exceeds the reservoir the object will be skipped. For further informations see ReservoirSampler.

ReservoirSample.RType

public ReservoirSample.RType(int reservoirSize,
                             ContinuousRandomWrapper cRandom,
                             DiscreteRandomWrapper dRandom)
Constructs a new object of the Rtype reservoir sampling strategy.

Parameters:
reservoirSize - size of the used reservoir
cRandom - pseudo random number generator (PRNG) delivering uniform distributed random numbers between 0.0d (inclusively) and 1.0d (exclusively).
dRandom - pseudo random number generator (PRNG) delivering equally discrete distributed random numbers between zero (inclusively) and any given integer (exclusively)

ReservoirSample.RType

public ReservoirSample.RType(int reservoirSize)
Constructs a new object of the Rtype reservoir sampling strategy. Using this constructor means using the Java Random Engine (which has a bad reputation). In package connectivity.colt wrappers for the usage with the Colt Library are available.

Parameters:
reservoirSize - size of the used reservoir
